m... he rubbed his head and groand.<br>
&quot;Where am I?&quot; He said to the darkness. He slowly Stood up and winced at each movement his body was sore.<br>
He slowly scanned the darkness letting his vision slowly slip Ultra Vision. He looked down examining himself for further injury. He was wearing torn rags of cloth. He stood straight and shook his head to clear the last few spots from his eyes. He looked around the strange cave. He had never been here before... or maybe he had... he shook his head and searched his mind for who he was and what he was doing in this strange place. He Grunted and began limpy slowly down a tunnel.. One direction seemed as good as another he thought. As he walked he noticed a slight incline in the tunnel the stuffy air was becoming cooler and more open. He slowly turned each bend in the long tunnel praying to see something besides the dull gray of the rocks. He suddenly found himself looking at darkness.. but not the stuffy pitch black of the tunnels.. it was a much lighter darkness for the young Drow was staring out of a cave  into the night lit by the stars... a night of the surface world. &quot;Where am I?&quot; He said again but, this time it was awe inspired. He stumbled out of the cave and onto a rocky path. He groaned loudly as a rock jabbed into his bruised leg. He stood up and shook it off. He began to walk under the trees  keeping the wall to his left. He walked into a large crevice. A heavily armed Drow approched him. &quot;Who are you?&quot; The Guard picked his sword up in  a threat. The boy stuttered &quot;I.. I... D..ddd..on't know who I am...&quot; The Guard looked confused. &quot;Stay here boy I shall be right back...&quot; The guard promptly turned around and looked for a Dragoon he had no idea what to do hopefully the higher ranking officer did. <br>
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
                         The drow watched the guard disappear into the night. He had no intention of staying around he decided to take his chances alone. He ran down the crevice through the canyon as fast as his feat would carry him. He turned a sharp corner and tripped over a rock. He was in luck though for the fall had saved him from a trip into the lava that was mearly inches from his face. The boy stood up and surveyed the area before him. It was a bright place the heat was intense lava surrounded him with thin walkways through the lava pulls prodvided his only way across. The drow was curious as he walked across the paths. He looked around and noted other people around him fighting strange creatures. He decided to stay hidden among the rocks as he passed them. He began a tedious trek across a large rimmed crater. Lava sizzled and bubbled below him. He looked around and saw three caves. He eyed the cave on his side of the crater and began to walk towards it. Just as he approached it a Goblin spotted him and began Loud Gibbering Taunts and threats at him widly running towards the drow. The young Dark Elf Turned and fled towards the tunnel praying that somone would help him the spindly legged goblin continued its hoots and curses as the drow turned into the tunnel and ran for all he was worth. He stumbled into a cave and fell before to large doors with all he had left he pushed with all his might but the door despite their large size they moved easily under the slightest touch. The drow fell into the cavern to the feet of to very surprised eurdites. They looked at the drow and then saw a fire goblin chasing after him. Both of the Wizards fell with in themselves and began to chant their hands going through Unique motions as the words of power climaxed and fired. The stunned goblin looked at it's feet it was only a foot away from its intended target. It then looked up and saw the wizards one with a grin and the other deep in the throes of casting. Then the goblin looked at its feet they were entiwned with roots. It new its doom and it went to its knees as a bolt of pure ice slammed into its heart spilling the pathetic creatures blood to the ground. <br>
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
          The Eurdites grinned as a vile creature fell to its doom. Then one turned to the curious drow at his feet. He looked to his sister in concern the drow was unconsicence. They each picked one end up of the dark elf and brought him before the of soulsek ro paladin. The paladin smiled and chanted a few words and layed his hands on the drow elf's Back.<br>
